ulltext · article · dec  · marketing lettersmarnik g dekimpedominique hanssensread fulltextall these events add to the customer equity of the firm and in this way a longterm customer equity effect of the original advertising emerges this longterm impact can be measured by persistence modeling as was done recently for an online service company in villanueva yoo and hanssens  this study found substantial differences in the lifetime values of customers acquired through different channels persistence models and marketing strategyshow abstract hide abstract abstract longrun marketingmix effectiveness lies at the heart of marketing strategies that try to create a sustainable competitive advantage for the brand or firm we review contributions in the area of persistence modeling and show how this approach allows to combine into one measure the net longrun impact of an initial marketing action in persistence modeling one traces the dynamic chain reaction of consumer response firm feedback and competititve reactions we provide both a short technical introduction to the technique and an overview of prevous applications and identify various other strategic questions for which persistence modeling may be particularly useful fulltext · article · marketing lettersmarnik g dekimpedominique hanssensread fulltextmodeling marketing dynamics by time series econometricsshow abstract hide abstract abstract this paper argues that timeseries econometrics provides valuable tools and opens exciting research opportunities to marketing researchers it allows marketing researchers to advance traditional modeling and estimation approaches by incorporating dynamic processes to answer new important research questions the authors discuss the challenges facing timeseries modelers in marketing provide an overview of recent methodological developments and several applications and highlight fruitful areas for future research this discussion is based on the first annual conference on ‘modeling marketing dynamics by time series econometrics’ at the tuck school of business at dartmouth hanover new hampshire usa on september –  copyright kluwer academic publishers  fulltext · article · feb  koen pauwelsimran s currimmarnik g dekimpe more authordominique hanssensread fulltextpeople who read this publication also readspecifics of marketing in the process of reintegration of slovak researchers fulltext · chapter · sep  · journal of research in marketing and entrepreneurshipviliam lendelanna zavodskaveronika šramováread fulltextthe effects of distributive procedural and interactional justice on customer retention an empirical investigation in the mobile telecom industry in tunisia fulltext · article · jul  nedra bahriammarianil bilgihanread fulltextan entrepreneurial relationship marketing approach to bb selling the case for intellectual capital sharingarticle · jun  donald p addison iitony linghamcan uslayolivia f leeolivia f leereaddata provided are for informational purposes only although carefully collected accuracy cannot be guaranteed publisher conditions are provided by romeo differing provisions from the publishers actual policy or licence agreement may be applicablethis publication is from a journal that may support self archivinglearn more   researchgate gmbh all rights reservedabout us · help center · careers · developers · news · contact us · privacy · terms · copyright  advertising · recruiting ordiscover by subject areajoin for freelog in people who read this publication also readchapter specifics of marketing in the process of reintegration of slovak researchers fulltext · sep read nowarticle the effects of distributive procedural and interactional justice on customer retention an empiric fulltext · jul  · journal of retailing and cread nowarticle an entrepreneurial relationship marketing approach to bb selling the case for intellectual capital jun  · journal of research in marread now